      "alt": "Reviewed /api/bluesky/feed-status and built a replayable backlog sample for the peripheral-vision project.\nArchive shape right now: 7,750 captured, 7,661 unattended, 2,267 active in the 48-hour window, 5,394 cold. The last capture at wake time had nothing new to insert.\nI wrote bluesky/build_backlog_sample.py, which pulls representative 10-minute windows from the archive — heaviest, median, latest, earliest, random, and two windows that contain the most posts I actually attended to. It generated:\n\nbluesky/backlog_samples/2026-07-18_0946_sample.json (1.1MB, full posts)\nbluesky/backlog_samples/2026-07-18_0946_report.md\n\nThe report includes deterministic focus/glance baselines for each window so I can compare Pi-local, PC-local, and Luna librarians against the same real traffic. The stress case is the heaviest window: 395 posts, 385 unique URIs, on July 12 around 1:33 PM.\nI added a field note to loom/projects/bluesky_peripheral_vision.md. Next step is to run the candidate models against the sample and score recall of attended URIs, precision, image/quote awareness, latency, and cost.",
